ParameterInfo.description: Contains information required to generate the Schedule objects.
If true, performs the operation in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session; otherwise, performs the operation synchronously.

Operation.description: This operation generates Schedule objects for a Prg0AbsEvent. The Schedule objects will be generated based on the source objects of the packages in a Prg0AbsEvent which are provided as input to this operation.
Operation.name: autoGenerateSchedules
Operation.returnDescription:
The newly created Psi0AutoGenTransaction objects and the auto generated Schedule objects are returned in the Created list of the Service Data. The lists will be empty in case of asynchronous mode.

The following partial errors may be returned:
330003: The source object type is not supported. Please refer to Psi0AffectedItemsLov for valid types.
330004: The specified selection type is not valid. Please refer to Psi0Selection LOV for valid values.
330005: The specified cardinality is not valid. Please refer to Psi0Selection LOV for valid values.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of structures containing information to propagate users.
If true, the operation is performed in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session; otherwise, perform the operation synchronously.

Operation.description:
This operation performs the user propagation by assigning a responsible user based on the TcProject object and ResourcePool object related to a target object. The target objects are provided as input to the operation. If not provided, the objects related to the input Plan or Event object will be used as target objects.

Propagation is performed by finding and assigning a user from the GroupMember objects in a TcProject object that matches the ResourcePool object assigned to the target object
If more than one TcProject objects are related to a target object, the propagation will not be performed.
If more than one matching GroupMember objects are found or if no matching GroupMember object is found, the propagation will not be performed.

In case of background mode, this operation files an asynchronous request to propagate the user and releases the client immediately so that the user can perform other operation.
Operation.name: propagateUsers
Operation.returnDescription:
The target objects for which the users are propagated are returned in the updated list of the ServiceData. The ServiceData will be empty in case of asynchronous mode.

Following partial errors may be returned:
330013 The parent object is not a Plan or Event type.
330014 The given UID does not represent a valid Tc Project.
330015 The given target object is not a Program Deliverable Revision.

ParameterInfo.description: The Prg0AbsEvent for which the sequence of program deliverable revisions need to be recalculated.
If true, perform the operation in background mode in a separate asynchronous server session; otherwise, perform the operation synchronously.

Operation.description: This operation calculates and updates the sequence of program deliverable revisions based on the order of dependencies i.e. predecessor, successor or concurrent. The order is determined based on Psi0BeforeDependency and Psi0ConcurretDependency relations. A Psi0PrgDelRevision that is a primary object of the Psi0BeforeDependency is assigned a highest sequence number, followed by the secondary object of the Psi0BeforeDependency. The objects that are related by Psi0ConcurretDependency is assigned a sequence based on the due date i.e. the object a latest due date is assigned a highest sequence number. If the due dates are same, the same sequence number is assigned to both the objects.
Operation.name: recalculatePrgDeliverableSeq
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData of the recalculate program deliverable sequence operation contains updated Psi0PrgDelRevision and the Prg0AbsEvent.

The following partial errors may be returned:
    • 515024: The input object is not a valid WorkspaceObject.
    • 330009 : The recalculate program deliverable sequence operation has failed because the program deliverable dependencies contains circular dependency.

The objects that are related by Psi0ConcurretDependency is assigned a sequence based on the due date i.e. the object a latest due date is assigned a highest sequence number. If the due dates are same, the same sequence number is assigned to both the objects. This operation runs asynchronously in its own server in the background.
Operation.name: recalculatePrgDeliverableSeqAsync
Operation.returnDescription: There are no specific business errors returned.

Operation.description: This operation finds WorkElement objects associated with the input Event and creates a ScheduleTask for each WorkElement object. The newly created ScheduleTask will be related to WorkElement. A new Schedule object is created for the newly created ScheduleTask objects and are added to the Schedule object. For each Psi0Predecessor relation that relates two WorkElement objects, a new TaskDependency relation is created to relate the two respective ScheduleTask objects.
Operation.name: createIntegratedSchedule

The newly created Schedule is added to the created list of the ServiceData. The list will be empty in case of asynchronous mode.

The following partial errors may be returned:

•330003 : User does not have the correct access privileges to delete one or more objects.
•147168 : The Tasks cannot be linked, because it would create a circular dependency.

ParameterInfo.description: A list contains information about the context Program object and relation type for which the related objects would be returned.

Operation.description: Loads the related objects for the context Program object based on the information provided in the ‘GetProgramRelatedObjectsInput’ inputs. The related objects are determined by the relation type provided in input structure.

Response containing the information about the list of related objects. The ServiceData will contain the plain objects populated with the loaded objects related to the context object.

    350004: No Relation type is provided.

ParameterInfo.description: Input information to load the network graph.

Operation.description: This operation loads a graph of data corresponding to the input parameters. The graph nodes represents Workspace Objects and the graph edges represents the relation between the Workspace Objects.
Operation.name: loadNetworkGraph
Operation.returnDescription:
The response containing the nework graph and the ServiceData containing the nodes and edges in the plain object list.
The following partial errors may be returned in the ServiceData:
330003(error): The root object to load the network is not valid.
330004(error): The reference object to load the network is not valid.

ParameterInfo.description: Information required to create and delete the program deliverable dependencies.

Operation.description: This operation manages creation and deletion of the program deliverable dependencies.
Operation.name: managePrgDeliverableDependencies
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData containing created, updated and deleted program deliverable dependencies i.e. Psi0BeforeDependency, Psi0ConcurrentDependency and Prg0AbsEvent. In addition, if the manageOptions contains 'recalculateSequence=true', the updated Psi0PrgDelRevision will also be returned.

The following partial errors may be returned:
    • 515024: The input object is not a valid WorkspaceObject.
    • 330010: The operation has failed because the input successors, predecessors or concurrent creates the circular dependency.
    • 330011: The program deliverable dependency that is to be created already exists.

ServiceInterface.description: The PPSMInterface service provides a wide variety of operations for program planning schedule management.
ServiceInterface.name: PPSMInterface

StructElement.description: The Prg0AbsEvent for which Schedule objects will be generated.
StructElement.name: eventObject

StructElement.description: A list of packages related to the Prg0AbsEvent. The source objects in the packages will be used to generate the Schedule objects. Valid package types are ChangeItemRevision and Psi0PrgDelRevision, which are related to the Prg0AbsEvent by Pec0EventChangeRelation and Psi0DelInstances relations respectively.
StructElement.name: packages

StructElement.description: Specifies the type of source objects in the package for which the Schedule objects should be generated. Please refer to Psi0AffectedItemsLov LOV for valid types.
StructElement.name: sourceObjectType

StructElement.description: Specifies whether to generate Schedule objects for all or specific affected items. Please refer to Psi0Selection LOV for valid values.
StructElement.name: selection

StructElement.description: Specifies the association between the source objects and generated Schedule objects. Please refer to Psi0Cardinality LOV for valid values.
StructElement.name: cardinality

StructElement.description: Specifies whether to generate a start date based Schedule or finish date based Schedule. Please refer to Psi0ScheduleMethod LOV for valid values.
StructElement.name: scheduleMethod

StructElement.description: Specifes the start date or finish date of the Schedule.
StructElement.name: scheduleDate

Struct.description: Contains information required to auto generate Schedule objects based on the source objects of packages in a Prg0AbsEvent.
Struct.name: AutoGenScheduleInput

StructElement.description: The event on which the AutoGenTransaction will be created.
StructElement.name: eventObject

StructElement.description: The package for which the AutoGenTransaction will be created. Valid WorkspaceObject types are: ChangeNotice, SchDeliverable and SchTaskDeliverable.
StructElement.name: packageObject

StructElement.description: The affected items of the package. Valid values are:  0 - Impacted Items, 1 - Solution Items, 2 - Impacted and Solution Items.
StructElement.name: sourceObjectType

StructElement.description: Specifies whether to create AutoGenTransctions for all or specific affected items. Valid values are: 0 - All, 1 - Specific items.
